Undergraduate Students (100-200 level courses)   The Cost of Attendance is determined annually considering survey and consumer price data.  These figures represent the typical expenses incurred by students; however, there may be special circumstances that warrant an evaluation of individual costs.  For example, aviation students or students that live with parents and pay rent.  Students may request an evaluation of their specific cost of attendance by completing a Budget Adjustment Request Form. Adjustments to Cost of Attendance For your student specific Cost of Attendance go to UAOnline; click on Financial Aid, Award, Award by Aid Year (select the appropriate year), and then click on Award Overview.   You must notify the OSFA if your enrollment has changed since receiving your initial award letter.
